<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1324,284,1470]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,1083,1109]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species appears to be closest to 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1075,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eriogonae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[917,1075,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">G. eriogonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1093,1187,1084,1110]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The males may be separated by the absence of a small spur on the venter of the gonocoxa in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="painteri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">G. painteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[320,411,1164,1190]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The vaginal furca in the female of 
<taxonomicName box="[825,954,1164,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="painteri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[825,954,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">G. painteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[969,1059,1164,1190]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a much more pronounced inward projecting ramus. These flies appear to be on the wing in southern Arizona in August, while other species occurring throughout the same range are found earlier in the year.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
